00:06:52.300 --> 00:06:53.820
You look so pretty in per…

00:06:56.000 --> 00:07:00.180
She’s a cop. That’s why I need her help on Uncle Thip’s case.

00:07:00.700 --> 00:07:01.820
I see.

00:07:02.380 --> 00:07:03.940
[So pretty]

00:07:04.130 --> 00:07:09.140
She’ll stay over tonight. Why don’t you go and get some rest first?

00:07:09.140 --> 00:07:11.180
It’s late. We can talk tomorrow.

00:07:11.560 --> 00:07:13.530
Okay then. See you tomorrow.

00:07:19.900 --> 00:07:21.020
Goodnight.

00:07:26.300 --> 00:07:27.300
Geez, what was that?

00:07:27.530 --> 00:07:31.340
What? She’s pretty so I compliment her. What’s wrong with it?

00:07:31.700 --> 00:07:34.260
It’s wrong because Rose isn’t your friend.

00:07:35.900 --> 00:07:40.700
Oh, I totally forgot that she’s your girl.

00:07:42.130 --> 00:07:44.420
Back off…or I’ll shoot you.

00:07:48.400 --> 00:07:50.530
Aren’t you going to tell her about what happened today?

00:07:51.860 --> 00:07:54.600
No, I don’t want to scare her.

00:07:59.159 --> 00:08:02.300
How very caring of you.

00:08:16.530 --> 00:08:19.300
What? You have to let them go?

00:08:23.820 --> 00:08:26.740
Okay, got it. Thanks a lot.

00:08:28.700 --> 00:08:29.530
How is it?

00:08:29.700 --> 00:08:31.800
They refused to tell us who sent them.

00:08:31.900 --> 00:08:34.260
They said they got sideswiped by your car, so they went after you to pay for it.

00:08:34.559 --> 00:08:36.059
Someone has already bailed them out.

00:08:38.400 --> 00:08:39.740
His backup is really powerful.

00:08:42.200 --> 00:08:44.730
That superintendent brat is probably one of them too.

00:08:45.160 --> 00:08:49.260
Hey, watch your mouth. Or you’ll be transferred somewhere far away again.

00:08:50.260 --> 00:08:53.560
Who cares? I’m not afraid of him. Who the hell does he think he is?

00:08:57.930 --> 00:08:59.160
Now what?

00:09:00.260 --> 00:09:05.460
At first, I thought this plan could’ve turned the situation in our favour.

00:09:06.760 --> 00:09:08.180
But since it has turned out like this,

00:09:08.620 --> 00:09:13.220
I guess I’ll have to find a way to take them down completely, just like what Uncle Thip tried to do.

00:09:14.160 --> 00:09:16.380
You’re going to fight them alone?

00:09:17.140 --> 00:09:19.020
I can’t let you risk yourself like that.

00:09:24.900 --> 00:09:29.060
Don’t worry, we have someone who can help us.

00:09:29.960 --> 00:09:30.760
Who?

00:09:31.660 --> 00:09:35.620
It’s Fah. The police mightn’t be able to help us but the journalist can.

00:09:36.260 --> 00:09:39.460
I’ll do anything to expose them and their illicit trade.

00:09:44.700 --> 00:09:45.580
Excuse me.

00:09:45.580 --> 00:09:50.980
You’ve called the right person, Din. My team and I are working on this case.

00:09:50.980 --> 00:09:55.620
We’ve received a lot of messages from the followers on our page that many girls have been missing lately.

00:09:55.700 --> 00:09:59.620
But some of them are willing to do it. Like those girls on my farm.

00:09:59.620 --> 00:10:02.500
They told their parents it’s a surrogacy job.

00:10:02.860 --> 00:10:06.220
But eventually, their relatives couldn’t get a hold of them.

00:10:07.930 --> 00:10:09.960
I sent someone to spy on them and gather more information.

00:10:11.160 --> 00:10:13.260
We found out that it’s human trafficking.

00:10:13.500 --> 00:10:15.660
They’re smuggling girls to our neighboring countries.

00:10:16.130 --> 00:10:19.500
[Fah]: But we still don’t have enough information that’d get us to the last boss.

00:10:20.660 --> 00:10:23.160
I’m sure those men are working for Mr. Wasupol.

00:10:23.800 --> 00:10:25.660
I want you to help us expose them.

00:10:26.730 --> 00:10:28.960
Sure. Let’s trade our information.

00:10:29.360 --> 00:10:34.020
I’ll send you everything I know, in case Lom might be able to look further into it.

00:10:41.180 --> 00:10:43.100
[Chaing Rai Case]

00:10:46.560 --> 00:10:49.780
That Wasupol is a complete bastard.

00:10:51.800 --> 00:10:55.780
If he can finally get his hands on Chomchan farm, he’d probably be fearless.

00:10:57.000 --> 00:11:02.740
With this much benefit, I’m sure he’d do anything to acquire that land.

00:11:04.760 --> 00:11:09.220
I have to make Wasu change his target, so that he’d leave Rose alone.

00:11:11.400 --> 00:11:12.530
That’s easy.

00:11:14.460 --> 00:11:18.300
If he wants to marry Rose because he wants the land on her farm,

00:11:19.130 --> 00:11:23.300
then don’t let him marry her, and she’ll be safe.

00:11:26.060 --> 00:11:29.540
That’s easy for you to say. But how?

00:11:32.160 --> 00:11:35.180
Well, as long as Rose agrees…

00:11:37.400 --> 00:11:41.940
Agree? Agree to what?

00:11:43.460 --> 00:11:45.200
You have to marry Rose.

00:11:47.900 --> 00:11:51.700
Make them think she gives you her farm.

00:11:52.730 --> 00:11:57.260
And that it’s you who owns everything, not her.

00:11:57.930 --> 00:12:01.740
Trust me, they’ll surely go crazy like a mad dog.

00:12:03.560 --> 00:12:04.760
I don’t think she’ll agree.

00:12:05.760 --> 00:12:08.200
But this is the only way to keep her safe.

00:12:29.420 --> 00:12:31.180
I’m waiting for you, Dad.

00:12:32.760 --> 00:12:35.300
Please wake up soon and give me a hug.

00:12:40.980 --> 00:12:42.420
[Door knocking]

00:12:45.060 --> 00:12:47.340
Excuse me, the doctor would like to talk to the relative.

00:12:49.700 --> 00:12:51.500
You go then, I’ll stay here with Uncle.

00:12:53.060 --> 00:12:54.580
Thank you, Din.

00:13:20.360 --> 00:13:21.400
Uncle Thip…

00:13:24.530 --> 00:13:32.940
If I’m going to fix this situation by marrying Rose, will you be okay with it?

00:13:49.160 --> 00:13:51.200
What did the doctor say?

00:13:54.200 --> 00:13:58.340
He said Dad might still be in this condition for a while.

00:14:00.400 --> 00:14:05.300
You visit him almost every day. I think Uncle knows it somehow.

00:14:05.560 --> 00:14:08.220
I’m sure he’ll get better and be able to give you a hug soon.

00:14:10.200 --> 00:14:11.560
Thank you, Din.

00:14:13.600 --> 00:14:17.400
Is there anywhere you want to go next? I’ll take you there.

00:14:20.000 --> 00:14:21.860
I want to go to Chomchan farm.

00:15:02.530 --> 00:15:05.000
I want to put these roses in a vase in my house.

00:15:05.600 --> 00:15:08.300
So that it’d make me feel as if my parents were still near.

00:15:15.800 --> 00:15:17.400
Come, let me do it for you.

00:15:20.900 --> 00:15:21.700
Thank you.

00:15:49.700 --> 00:15:50.730
Rose.

00:15:52.260 --> 00:15:53.060
Yes?

00:16:07.560 --> 00:16:08.360
Thank you.

00:16:40.330 --> 00:16:41.820
Please marry me.

00:16:48.260 --> 00:16:51.100
Please marry me, Rose.

00:16:56.580 --> 00:16:57.780
Rose!

00:17:03.620 --> 00:17:06.619
[Little Rabbit: Miss you so much. When are you coming back?]

00:17:06.619 --> 00:17:10.619
[Lom: Come to Chiang Rai then. I’ll take you around.]

00:17:10.859 --> 00:17:13.780
Hi, Rose. Rose?

00:17:14.930 --> 00:17:15.730
Rose!

00:17:20.900 --> 00:17:22.420
She can’t see me?

00:17:31.960 --> 00:17:35.700
Hey, what’s wrong with Rose? Is Uncle Thip getting worse?

00:17:39.160 --> 00:17:42.940
It’s not Uncle Tip. It’s me who’s in trouble.

00:17:45.060 --> 00:17:45.960
What is it?

00:17:48.060 --> 00:17:54.860
You suggested I should marry Rose, right? I don’t think this plan would work anymore.

00:17:56.000 --> 00:17:56.800
Why?

00:17:59.200 --> 00:18:01.560
I don’t think she’d want to marry me.

00:18:04.360 --> 00:18:09.220
Don’t tell me…Did you already propose to her?

00:18:20.560 --> 00:18:25.460
Serve you right. Now I know why she quickly walked away like that. Crystal clear.

00:18:26.530 --> 00:18:27.460
What did I do wrong?

00:18:27.600 --> 00:18:29.330
Everything. You still have the guts to ask?

00:18:30.460 --> 00:18:33.300
Suddenly proposing to her like that, who wouldn’t be in shock?

00:18:33.760 --> 00:18:36.260
You should’ve come and asked your life coach first.

00:18:36.960 --> 00:18:38.300
What should I tell her then?

00:18:38.730 --> 00:18:43.620
You have to explain to her about our plan first. Tell her why you want to marry her.

00:18:43.620 --> 00:18:47.420
Tell her you have to marry her because you want to help her.

00:18:49.360 --> 00:18:52.260
But I don’t even have the courage to tell her about what happened yesterday.

00:18:52.530 --> 00:18:58.340
If she finds out that I’m using myself as bait, she’ll definitely say no.

00:18:58.360 --> 00:18:59.940
And do you think she’d say yes to this?

00:19:00.600 --> 00:19:03.460
She probably thinks you’ve gone nuts by now.

00:19:06.100 --> 00:19:07.380
So…What should I do then?

00:19:07.380 --> 00:19:09.660
Should I go and explain everything to her now?

00:19:10.100 --> 00:19:12.900
Not yet. Give her some time.

00:19:12.900 --> 00:19:17.700
What you should do now is to come up with a good reason to make her agree to marry you.

00:19:18.000 --> 00:19:22.260
It’s not too late, isn’t it? Wouldn’t she think I’m not right in the head by now?

00:19:23.800 --> 00:19:25.020
Lom. Lom.

00:19:25.020 --> 00:19:27.180
- Suit yourself then.
- Lom, wait. Lom!

00:19:28.160 --> 00:19:30.860
Hey! Lom!

00:19:52.130 --> 00:19:54.500
[Rose: A prince must be with a princess.]

00:19:55.600 --> 00:19:58.600
[Rose: Will the prince marry this princess from the land of rose?]

00:19:59.600 --> 00:20:01.360
[Din: What kind of a princess proposes to a prince first?]

00:20:01.900 --> 00:20:03.200
[Rose: Din!]

00:20:04.300 --> 00:20:05.460
[Din: Yes, I’ll marry you.]

00:20:09.930 --> 00:20:13.460
[Din: Rose, will you marry me?]

00:20:15.130 --> 00:20:18.300
[Din: Please marry me, Rose.]

00:20:44.000 --> 00:20:47.940
[Lom: She probably thinks you’ve gone nuts by now.]

00:20:55.560 --> 00:20:57.960
[Din: Please marry me, Rose.]

00:21:47.300 --> 00:21:49.200
- I'll use these to make you some salad.
- Sounds good.

00:21:50.530 --> 00:21:51.330
Din.

00:21:59.860 --> 00:22:01.940
Are you leaving, Miss?

00:22:02.260 --> 00:22:04.500
Why don’t you stay for breakfast with Miss Rose first?

00:22:04.800 --> 00:22:07.800
Maybe not. I have a lot to take care of today.

00:22:08.130 --> 00:22:09.540
You’re not avoiding her, aren’t you?

00:22:11.160 --> 00:22:12.960
Avoiding? Who is she avoiding?

00:22:13.900 --> 00:22:16.060
Don’t listen to her nonsense, Aunt Chan.

00:22:17.130 --> 00:22:18.460
Morning, Rose!

00:22:20.700 --> 00:22:23.100
Well, I’m…I’m going then.

00:22:26.700 --> 00:22:27.930
- Miss Lom.
- Yes?

00:22:28.200 --> 00:22:29.260
What is going on?

00:22:29.700 --> 00:22:34.620
Oh, I’m so hungry now. Let’s go eat. I want to eat some vegetables.

00:22:34.620 --> 00:22:38.020
I’ll make you salad then. But you have to tell me everything.

00:22:48.530 --> 00:22:49.380
Moddang!

00:22:49.380 --> 00:22:50.580
What are you doing, Miss?

00:22:51.130 --> 00:22:51.980
Get in here first.

00:22:51.980 --> 00:22:53.580
What happened, Miss?

00:22:54.530 --> 00:22:55.330
What is it?

00:22:58.400 --> 00:22:59.860
What’s wrong, Miss?

00:23:00.000 --> 00:23:02.130
Moddang, I don’t know what to do now.

00:23:02.460 --> 00:23:03.530
What happened?

00:23:03.800 --> 00:23:04.930
Yesterday, Din…

00:23:05.130 --> 00:23:07.900
Miss Din what? Did she and Mr. Wasu fight again?

00:23:08.000 --> 00:23:09.180
No, not him.

00:23:09.180 --> 00:23:10.660
Din just…

00:23:10.660 --> 00:23:11.580
Yes?

00:23:11.620 --> 00:23:12.760
She…

00:23:13.200 --> 00:23:13.700
Yes?

00:23:13.700 --> 00:23:14.930
She…

00:23:15.060 --> 00:23:15.860
Yes?

00:23:16.300 --> 00:23:17.700
She proposed to me!

00:23:20.660 --> 00:23:24.700
See? You already look so stunned just by hearing it.

00:23:27.900 --> 00:23:30.820
She proposed. Miss Din proposed to you!

00:23:30.820 --> 00:23:32.260
Miss Din proposed to you!

00:23:32.360 --> 00:23:36.700
She seems quiet on the outside, but she’s actually down bad for you much more than I thought.

00:23:36.700 --> 00:23:40.140
It’s been only a few days after you came back and she’s already proposed to you!

00:23:41.400 --> 00:23:42.560
Stop talking rubbish.

00:23:42.760 --> 00:23:45.780
What rubbish, Miss? It’s all true.

00:23:45.780 --> 00:23:49.460
Remember that day when you first came back? She was right there to protect you.

00:23:49.460 --> 00:23:52.500
Or the other day after that incident on our farm, she also asked you to move in with her.

00:23:52.500 --> 00:23:54.130
And now she even proposed to you too!

00:23:54.300 --> 00:23:58.940
If it were me, I’d definitely say ‘Yes!’ without even thinking.

00:23:59.660 --> 00:24:03.140
How can I marry her? We’re not lovers.

00:24:03.360 --> 00:24:08.060
Aw, look at those people in the past, Miss. You’ll grow to love her soon after marriage.

00:24:08.130 --> 00:24:09.260
But I’m not like those in the past.

00:24:09.600 --> 00:24:10.800
I’m a gen-Z girl.

00:24:11.400 --> 00:24:15.580
Geez, who cares about that? Miss Din is such a sweet person.

00:24:15.580 --> 00:24:20.260
Whoever has the chance to be close to her will definitely fall for her.

00:24:20.260 --> 00:24:22.800
Whatever. I’m not going to do it.

00:24:24.200 --> 00:24:26.140
Why not, Miss?

00:24:26.140 --> 00:24:30.940
Miss Din is considered top-tier around here. Rawr!

00:24:31.100 --> 00:24:33.660
No! I’ve decided.

00:24:33.900 --> 00:24:36.540
I’m going to be clear and tell her I won’t marry her.

00:24:36.560 --> 00:24:38.730
That’s such a waste, Miss. Please think it over a little.

00:24:39.600 --> 00:24:40.760
Moddang. No.

00:24:43.530 --> 00:24:46.020
Geez, why is it so hard to ship them together?

00:24:46.900 --> 00:24:49.980
Miss Rose! Please think about it again!

00:24:55.530 --> 00:24:56.660
Aunt Chan.

00:24:57.100 --> 00:24:57.900
Yes?

00:24:59.100 --> 00:25:00.160
Have you seen Din?

00:25:00.330 --> 00:25:02.420
She should be in the office by now.

00:25:02.420 --> 00:25:06.740
And Miss Lom has gone to the city centre. They’ll probably be back in the evening.

00:25:06.960 --> 00:25:08.580
Is the office far from here?

00:25:08.800 --> 00:25:12.500
Not at all. It’s that way, just less than 10-minute walk.

00:25:13.700 --> 00:25:14.500
Thank you.

00:25:15.160 --> 00:25:17.700
Oh, are you going to go there now, Miss?

00:25:19.300 --> 00:25:22.260
The sun is quite strong outside. I’ll tell Miss Din to come here instead.

00:25:22.600 --> 00:25:25.200
It’s all right. I can walk there.

00:25:32.730 --> 00:25:34.760
Miss Rose, I’ll go with you too.

00:25:35.730 --> 00:25:38.360
It’s quite hot. Let’s stay under the umbrella.

00:25:38.660 --> 00:25:40.800
Not hot at all. You’re just being nosy, aren’t you?

00:25:40.980 --> 00:25:45.800
Of course not. Miss Din told me I shouldn’t let you go anywhere alone.

00:25:46.400 --> 00:25:49.980
You’ve only been here a few days and she’s already bought you off?

00:25:50.000 --> 00:25:51.980
Oh, she doesn’t have to do that.

00:25:51.980 --> 00:25:57.020
Just by seeing her face, I’m willing to go through heaven and hell for her.

00:25:57.020 --> 00:25:59.060
Moddang! She’s not someone you can joke around like that.

00:25:59.330 --> 00:25:59.940
Behave yourself.

00:25:59.940 --> 00:26:01.900
Oh, are you jealous?

00:26:01.930 --> 00:26:04.100
Wait for me, Miss!

00:26:04.200 --> 00:26:05.860
Please don’t be upset.

00:26:21.060 --> 00:26:23.160
Is she really in the office?

00:26:23.600 --> 00:26:24.530
I can’t see her anywhere.

00:26:25.500 --> 00:26:27.530
But Aunt Chan said she’s here.

00:26:28.700 --> 00:26:32.160
Load them on the truck with the rest of the fertilizers too.

00:26:34.000 --> 00:26:35.900
Oh, hello, Miss Rose.

00:26:36.620 --> 00:26:37.700
Hello.

00:26:38.540 --> 00:26:40.580
What are you doing here, Miss?

00:26:43.660 --> 00:26:46.500
Er…I’m Kla, head of the workers here.

00:26:47.300 --> 00:26:49.500
You know who I am?

00:26:51.220 --> 00:26:56.140
Yes, Miss. Miss Din told me to take care of you if you ever come to visit here.

00:26:56.140 --> 00:27:02.460
She said it’s very easy to know it’s you since you’re very beautiful. So, I’d be able to know right away.

00:27:04.360 --> 00:27:08.700
Maybe it’s easier if she introduces me to everyone here.

00:27:10.760 --> 00:27:11.560
I thought so too, Miss.

00:27:12.460 --> 00:27:14.160
So, where is she now?

00:27:14.700 --> 00:27:17.730
She has gone to the city centre with Kaew.

00:27:18.460 --> 00:27:22.620
When she’s back, I’ll tell her that you came looking for her, Miss.

00:27:22.940 --> 00:27:25.100
Please excuse me then, I must get back to work.

00:27:25.130 --> 00:27:25.930
Yes, thank you.

00:27:26.000 --> 00:27:27.060
You’re welcome.

00:27:29.600 --> 00:27:31.060
- Is it fresh?
- Yes.

00:27:34.160 --> 00:27:34.960
Who’s Kaew?

00:27:36.130 --> 00:27:39.900
She’s Miss Din’s assistant, and also Mr. Kla’s daughter.

00:27:40.600 --> 00:27:42.360
I see. An assistant.

00:27:44.500 --> 00:27:50.260
Yes. But they are very close. They’ve been friends since they were still in school.

00:27:51.460 --> 00:27:55.020
After she graduated, Miss Din asked her to help with the work here.

00:27:55.020 --> 00:27:58.140
She helps Miss Din taking care of this farm.

00:27:58.140 --> 00:28:01.260
If you see Miss Din anywhere, you’ll also see Miss Kaew there.

00:28:03.930 --> 00:28:05.940
They seem close indeed.

00:28:06.860 --> 00:28:11.460
But don’t worry, Miss. Although they might be really close,

00:28:11.460 --> 00:28:13.740
they’re just friends and nothing more.

00:28:17.600 --> 00:28:21.260
Why are you so quiet? Is it because you’re jealous?

00:28:23.660 --> 00:28:29.020
Why would I be jealous? I’m just curious. If Din and Miss Kaew are that close,

00:28:29.020 --> 00:28:33.180
why didn’t she propose to her then? Why proposed to me?

00:28:37.160 --> 00:28:38.460
Jealous for sure!

00:28:39.500 --> 00:28:41.460
Miss Rose, wait for me too!

00:28:43.800 --> 00:28:47.540
Hi, Rose. Aunt Chan said you went looking for Din.

00:28:47.540 --> 00:28:50.060
Why are you back alone? Is Din still working?

00:28:50.530 --> 00:28:52.360
She’s gone out with Miss Kaew since noon.

00:28:54.500 --> 00:28:59.400
I mean, she’s gone out for work since early morning.

00:29:00.400 --> 00:29:04.160
Perhaps…is there something bothering your mind?

00:29:05.360 --> 00:29:06.160
Yes?

00:29:09.360 --> 00:29:11.360
Is it about Din’s marriage proposal?

00:29:14.330 --> 00:29:16.200
You know about it too?

00:29:18.000 --> 00:29:24.300
Yes. How should I say it? Well, it was actually my idea.

00:29:25.700 --> 00:29:27.160
What do you mean?

00:29:28.730 --> 00:29:32.220
It means I told her to do that.

00:29:32.220 --> 00:29:37.380
I told her that marrying you would be the best way to keep you safe from Mr. Wasupol’s harm.

00:29:38.760 --> 00:29:41.700
Safe? How?

00:29:42.600 --> 00:29:46.340
If you agree to marry Din, everyone would think that…

00:29:46.340 --> 00:29:50.820
Din now owns everything instead of you. That’d make you safer.

00:29:50.820 --> 00:29:56.300
At least, this means Mr. Wasupol will no longer have any excuse to make you marry his son.

00:29:57.160 --> 00:30:03.330
So, Din proposed to me because it was a plan that you suggested?

00:30:05.860 --> 00:30:10.020
Hmm…yes.

00:30:12.060 --> 00:30:15.330
She isn’t quite good at communicating. That might’ve made you misunderstand her.

00:30:18.660 --> 00:30:23.300
I also find it strange for her to suddenly propose to me like that.

00:30:24.330 --> 00:30:28.760
Now that you know the truth, will you agree to marry her?

00:30:30.500 --> 00:30:32.500
I really appreciate your concern, Lom.

00:30:33.600 --> 00:30:36.760
But for me, marriage must come after love.

00:30:38.200 --> 00:30:40.930
But if we have to wait for you to fall in love, it might already be too late.

00:30:41.860 --> 00:30:44.160
Also, it’s just a fake marriage.

00:30:45.000 --> 00:30:48.460
But I don’t want Din to sacrifice that much and put herself in danger for me.

00:30:49.200 --> 00:30:51.660
I’ve already caused her much enough problems.

00:30:53.560 --> 00:30:55.860
But Din chose to do it herself.

00:30:57.560 --> 00:31:02.060
Thank you, Lom. I’ll think about it.

00:31:33.600 --> 00:31:35.460
Aren’t you sleepy, Miss?

00:31:38.100 --> 00:31:40.580
I can barely keep my eyes open now.

00:31:44.400 --> 00:31:47.780
Just go to bed then. You don’t have to wait with me.

00:31:48.330 --> 00:31:50.000
But Miss Din said…

00:31:50.460 --> 00:31:56.020
Moddang, just go to sleep. I can wait for her alone.

00:31:56.660 --> 00:32:03.780
Well, then…please don’t stay up so late, Miss.

00:32:56.400 --> 00:32:58.660
I wish you would wake up soon, Dad.

00:32:59.730 --> 00:33:01.400
I’m so confused right now.

00:33:34.360 --> 00:33:37.530
The light in the house is still on. Miss Rose is probably waiting for you.

00:33:38.400 --> 00:33:42.540
Rose? I don’t think so.

00:33:44.500 --> 00:33:47.100
Excuse me for prying, but are you two having a problem?

00:33:48.200 --> 00:33:51.960
When we were with the client today, I noticed you were quite distracted.

00:33:54.560 --> 00:33:55.360
It’s nothing.

00:33:56.960 --> 00:33:59.860
I’m sorry I didn’t help you drive today.

00:34:00.860 --> 00:34:05.360
Kaew, I never think of you as an assistant. You’re my friend.

00:34:07.500 --> 00:34:10.860
So, how’s your wrist? Is it better?

00:34:13.659 --> 00:34:16.699
Much better now. Not that hurt anymore, Miss.

00:34:17.659 --> 00:34:21.100
I’ll try to get back to normal soon so that I can drive for you.

00:34:21.580 --> 00:34:24.500
What about your forehead?

00:34:24.860 --> 00:34:29.460
It’s getting less swollen now.

00:34:29.560 --> 00:34:31.300
Yeah, the red mark has gone.

00:34:31.600 --> 00:34:32.400
Din!

00:34:34.730 --> 00:34:35.940
Rose.

00:34:38.400 --> 00:34:40.380
This is Kaew, my assistant.

00:34:41.199 --> 00:34:42.330
Hello, Miss Rose.

00:34:42.760 --> 00:34:43.860
Hello, Miss Kaew.

00:34:47.260 --> 00:34:50.340
Don’t you think you’re overworking Miss Kaew?

00:34:50.340 --> 00:34:53.460
It’s almost midnight but she still can’t get off work.

00:34:53.500 --> 00:34:57.820
Oh, not at all. I’m used to it. You have to be quite flexible when working with her.

00:34:59.700 --> 00:35:02.660
You seem to know her so well, Miss Kaew.

00:35:06.130 --> 00:35:08.980
So, how come you’re still up?

00:35:09.400 --> 00:35:10.860
I’m waiting for you.

00:35:12.100 --> 00:35:15.330
Me? Why?

00:35:16.460 --> 00:35:18.660
To continue where we left off.

00:35:18.660 --> 00:35:21.900
I won’t be able to sleep if we don’t clear it up.

00:35:25.700 --> 00:35:29.530
I’d better head home then, so that you and her can talk.

00:35:30.500 --> 00:35:36.780
That’s all right, Miss Kaew. Since you’re her assistant and very close to her, you’re welcome to stay.

00:35:49.260 --> 00:35:51.130
It’s about your marriage proposal.

00:35:53.130 --> 00:35:56.560
Well, actually…I can explain about that, Rose.

00:35:56.730 --> 00:36:02.860
You don’t have to. Just listen to me. I already have an answer.

00:36:06.860 --> 00:36:10.820
I will marry you. We’ll get married as soon as possible.

00:36:31.700 --> 00:36:33.180
Lom. Lom!

00:36:33.180 --> 00:36:34.020
Lom, Lom, Lom, Lom!

00:36:34.020 --> 00:36:37.060
Lom! Wake up! Wake up, Lom!

00:36:37.060 --> 00:36:39.500
- Wake up!
- What?

00:36:39.500 --> 00:36:41.660
Rose just agreed to marry me!

00:36:41.960 --> 00:36:42.760
What?

00:36:42.960 --> 00:36:45.420
Rose agreed to marry me!

00:36:45.420 --> 00:36:46.060
Really?

00:36:46.060 --> 00:36:48.420
Yes! What should I do next?

00:36:48.460 --> 00:36:50.860
Where should I have the wedding? At a hotel or maybe

00:36:50.860 --> 00:36:51.700
Stop!

00:36:54.960 --> 00:36:57.340
It’s midnight. Calm down.

00:36:57.860 --> 00:36:58.660
Calm down.

00:36:59.500 --> 00:37:00.600
I was a little too happy.

00:37:01.340 --> 00:37:03.700
As if you were going to marry for real, huh?

00:37:04.260 --> 00:37:06.460
Isn’t it just a fake marriage?

00:37:07.060 --> 00:37:11.900
But even so, we have to make it as best as we can to show Rose that we are respectful.

00:37:12.380 --> 00:37:14.780
Roger that, Miss groom-to-be.

00:37:15.600 --> 00:37:18.540
I’m going back to sleep then. I’ll congratulate you tomorrow.

00:37:18.700 --> 00:37:21.400
Hey, wait! Lom, wait!

00:37:21.930 --> 00:37:23.620
Lom! Wake up!

00:37:23.800 --> 00:37:25.580
Who am I going to talk to then?

00:37:26.260 --> 00:37:27.060
Wake up!

00:37:27.500 --> 00:37:29.940
- Lom!
- Geez, so noisy!

00:37:29.940 --> 00:37:32.620
Hey, wake up. I can’t sleep, Lom.

00:37:35.560 --> 00:37:37.260
What the heck have I done?

00:37:39.500 --> 00:37:41.140
It’s not true!

00:37:46.300 --> 00:37:48.980
How could I face her tomorrow?

00:38:15.560 --> 00:38:18.900
Rose, you’re up early.

00:38:19.860 --> 00:38:22.360
Yes, you too.

00:38:25.360 --> 00:38:26.780
- About last night…
- About last night…

00:38:27.700 --> 00:38:29.260
You go first.

00:38:31.300 --> 00:38:37.200
About last night, were you serious?

00:38:40.360 --> 00:38:43.400
Yes, I’m serious.

00:38:47.960 --> 00:38:51.800
Then, there’s a lot we have to talk about.

00:38:53.260 --> 00:38:54.330
Talk about what?

00:39:14.660 --> 00:39:19.620
Hey, don’t be so serious. We’re not married for real anyway.

00:39:20.500 --> 00:39:25.100
Of course, I have to be serious. Although it’s a fake marriage, we have to make everyone believe we’re married for real.

00:39:25.100 --> 00:39:27.700
Otherwise, our plan would mean nothing.

00:39:29.600 --> 00:39:31.300
What do I have to do then?

00:39:33.700 --> 00:39:37.900
First, we must keep it a secret.

00:39:37.900 --> 00:39:40.820
Don’t let anyone know it’s a fake marriage.

00:39:41.000 --> 00:39:42.460
Not even Moddang?

00:39:42.900 --> 00:39:43.700
Yes.

00:39:45.000 --> 00:39:46.200
What about Miss Kaew?

00:39:46.860 --> 00:39:48.340
I won’t tell her too.

00:39:48.660 --> 00:39:53.620
She’ll only know that we’re having conflicts with Nubanun farm. But she’ll never know about our fake marriage.

00:39:54.930 --> 00:39:55.730
Okay.

00:39:56.200 --> 00:39:59.420
Right now, we can’t trust anyone.

00:39:59.420 --> 00:40:03.820
I believe there’s a mole on our farm who keeps informing Wasu about us.

00:40:04.260 --> 00:40:05.700
I promise I won’t tell anyone.

00:40:06.330 --> 00:40:13.060
Right now, apart from you and me, there are also Nam, Lom, and Fai whom I’ll tell them about this secret.

00:40:14.260 --> 00:40:17.900
Everyone in my family will also welcome you as one of the Watinwanich.

00:40:18.460 --> 00:40:22.180
So that you can rest assured you’re not facing this problem alone.

00:40:22.760 --> 00:40:24.400
Everyone will help protect you.

00:40:26.460 --> 00:40:27.260
Thank you.

00:40:29.860 --> 00:40:31.730
Is there anything else?

00:40:34.060 --> 00:40:38.380
Second, no matter where you go or whatever you do,

00:40:38.700 --> 00:40:41.140
you should always let me know.

00:40:41.140 --> 00:40:43.620
And I’ll also do the same to you.

00:40:43.760 --> 00:40:44.460
Yes.

00:40:44.460 --> 00:40:48.180
I’ll do my best to arrange our wedding and make it look as real as possible.

00:40:48.180 --> 00:40:49.100
Also…

00:40:51.760 --> 00:40:52.960
Also what?

00:40:55.100 --> 00:41:02.300
Also, we have to sign a certificate of marriage to make it legal.

00:41:02.300 --> 00:41:05.540
So that Wasu and his dad will believe us.

00:41:07.900 --> 00:41:10.300
But you don’t have to worry.

00:41:10.300 --> 00:41:15.740
I’ll write a contract stating that I’ll never touch any of your assets or properties.

00:41:16.020 --> 00:41:20.740
Or if you want, you can divorce me anytime.

00:41:24.200 --> 00:41:32.000
That’s fine. I understand we have to make it look real, both by law and in practice.

00:41:34.900 --> 00:41:40.340
In practice? Do you really know what that means?

00:41:45.160 --> 00:41:46.130
Of course, I do.

00:41:51.000 --> 00:42:00.100
Finally, if you ever meet someone you love and want to cancel this marriage,

00:42:00.780 --> 00:42:02.620
you can always let me know.

00:42:04.700 --> 00:42:05.420
Yes.

00:42:06.060 --> 00:42:10.020
If one day, you have someone you love and want to cancel this marriage,

00:42:10.020 --> 00:42:11.940
you can always let me know too.

00:42:13.700 --> 00:42:14.500
Deal.

00:42:27.060 --> 00:42:31.020
[Din: One day, I’ll become strong and protect you, Rose.]

00:42:31.020 --> 00:42:32.300
[Din: I promise.]

00:42:32.960 --> 00:42:33.930
[Rose: You promise!]

00:42:52.960 --> 00:42:55.060
Is she really going to marry you as soon as possible?

00:42:55.400 --> 00:42:57.980
Yes. And since you’re the one who came up with this plan,

00:42:58.020 --> 00:43:00.500
you have to be responsible by helping me arrange the wedding.

00:43:01.000 --> 00:43:03.000
Nope! I’m a cop not a wedding planner.

00:43:03.060 --> 00:43:06.260
- No way. No.
- Hey,wait. Hold it right there.

00:43:07.740 --> 00:43:10.730
Listen, you’re the most experienced one among our siblings.

00:43:11.180 --> 00:43:14.220
You’re a pro in this, with the most experience and the most flings.

00:43:14.340 --> 00:43:18.860
You must know what people who are going to marry want, or what they have to do.

00:43:20.000 --> 00:43:25.100
It’s true that I have a lot of flings. But so far, I haven’t met anyone I want to marry yet.

00:43:25.530 --> 00:43:27.060
Why do you have to rub it in?

00:43:28.330 --> 00:43:33.940
Oh, what to do then?

00:43:35.300 --> 00:43:36.800
Why don’t you just ask Nam?

00:43:38.960 --> 00:43:43.940
She owns a hotel. She surely has arranged hundreds of weddings there. That one is the real pro.

00:43:44.860 --> 00:43:45.660
That’s right!

00:43:52.860 --> 00:43:54.260
Nam: I already know.

00:43:54.900 --> 00:43:56.960
Lom called and told me everything yesterday.

00:44:02.100 --> 00:44:03.160
Nam: Don’t worry, Din.

00:44:03.700 --> 00:44:06.100
I’ll arrange the best wedding for you.

00:44:07.100 --> 00:44:10.980
As for the venue, let me go there and take a look first.

00:44:12.300 --> 00:44:15.300
But it’s quite urgent. Are you sure you can do it?

00:44:15.600 --> 00:44:21.780
Nam: Easy peasy. I even used to arrange a wedding where the groom ran away in the middle of the ceremony.

00:44:22.500 --> 00:44:26.140
Then, please tell Fai for me. I can’t get a hold of her at all.

00:44:26.400 --> 00:44:29.130
Not sure if she’s stuck in the mine or on a deserted island somewhere.

00:44:30.500 --> 00:44:31.300
Okay.

00:44:35.260 --> 00:44:36.740
Fai: What did you say?

00:44:37.960 --> 00:44:40.100
What? Din is getting married?!

00:44:40.130 --> 00:44:43.020
With who? And when? Why? Can we trust that person?

00:44:43.360 --> 00:44:45.800
When did they fall in love? Why have I never heard about it?

00:44:52.400 --> 00:44:54.460
Nam will come here to take care of the venue.

00:44:54.560 --> 00:44:58.620
Mhm. But right now, you have to take care of yourself first.

00:44:59.800 --> 00:45:00.600
Huh?

00:45:33.460 --> 00:45:38.860
Although it’s just a fake marriage, I genuinely want this wedding…

00:45:39.980 --> 00:45:43.260
to be a good memory, and leave a great impression in your heart.

00:45:55.730 --> 00:45:57.260
Hello, Miss Din.

00:45:59.530 --> 00:46:00.330
This way, please.

00:46:13.600 --> 00:46:14.940
Excuse me?

00:46:15.100 --> 00:46:15.900
Yes?

00:46:20.600 --> 00:46:21.600
How is it, Miss?

00:46:26.760 --> 00:46:28.660
It fits you perfectly.

00:46:29.100 --> 00:46:33.780
If you like this style, you can also choose the colour and the fabric pattern.

00:46:35.600 --> 00:46:37.220
Does it really suit me?

00:46:37.800 --> 00:46:38.620
Yes.

00:46:39.100 --> 00:46:44.300
If you’re not sure, how about we ask Miss Din too?

00:47:39.500 --> 00:47:40.860
What do you think?

00:47:46.360 --> 00:47:47.620
Din.

00:47:50.860 --> 00:47:51.900
Din!

00:47:55.330 --> 00:47:56.130
Yes?

00:47:56.760 --> 00:47:59.300
I asked what you think about this dress.

00:48:16.300 --> 00:48:17.200
It’s beautiful.

00:48:20.100 --> 00:48:22.930
I think I’m going to put my hair up like this.

00:48:23.560 --> 00:48:27.620
And put on a slight makeup, so that it won’t look too flashy.

00:48:28.660 --> 00:48:30.760
You already look so pretty without makeup.

00:48:32.730 --> 00:48:38.580
You don’t have to compliment me. It’s just a fake marriage anyway.

00:48:42.330 --> 00:48:49.300
Even though it’s not real, you’re the most beautiful bride in my eyes.

00:49:29.660 --> 00:49:31.340
I’m sorry.

00:49:32.360 --> 00:49:34.100
It was my fault, I tripped.

00:49:35.300 --> 00:49:39.300
I’d…better go change then.

00:49:43.400 --> 00:49:44.930
Can we stay like this for a while?

00:50:27.960 --> 00:50:32.820
I know why you brought me here, but…

00:50:32.960 --> 00:50:34.180
I know.

00:50:35.530 --> 00:50:37.500
But even if it’s just a fake marriage,

00:50:38.760 --> 00:50:41.660
I honestly want the best for you.

00:50:44.220 --> 00:50:45.580
[Door knocking]

00:50:52.600 --> 00:50:53.460
Hello.

00:51:06.160 --> 00:51:08.730
Please feel free and choose any ring that you like.

00:51:12.060 --> 00:51:12.860
Thank you.

00:51:29.500 --> 00:51:30.600
Maybe this one.

00:51:32.860 --> 00:51:35.660
It’s quite simple. I can wear it every day.

00:51:39.160 --> 00:51:41.000
Can we try that one, please?

00:51:41.160 --> 00:51:41.960
Yes.

00:52:25.600 --> 00:52:26.700
It fits.

00:52:29.800 --> 00:52:34.100
Then, I’ll take a similar one so that we can have a matching ring.

00:52:38.060 --> 00:52:40.260
This one please.

00:52:40.660 --> 00:52:41.530
Yes.

00:53:13.060 --> 00:53:15.660
I didn’t expect you’d invest so much for this wedding.

00:53:17.060 --> 00:53:18.900
We have to make it look real as much as possible.

00:53:19.700 --> 00:53:23.060
Thank you so much…for doing this much for me.

00:53:25.500 --> 00:53:31.100
Like I told you, I really want it to be a wonderful memory for both of us.

00:53:44.580 --> 00:53:45.500
Go!

00:53:47.660 --> 00:53:51.260
Why did you stop me, Dad? I was about to get rid of that bastard.

00:53:51.300 --> 00:53:54.460
Get a grip on yourself. You can’t go around and cause more trouble.

00:53:54.540 --> 00:53:55.330
I don’t care!

00:53:55.660 --> 00:53:58.740
If anyone dares to steal what’s mine, I’ll kill them!

00:54:00.300 --> 00:54:01.100
So what?

00:54:02.400 --> 00:54:04.700
Are you going to blow her head right here in broad daylight?

00:54:05.660 --> 00:54:09.500
Right now, the police–especially that Wayo girl–are keeping an eye on us.

00:54:10.360 --> 00:54:12.260
Don’t do anything recklessly.

00:54:13.530 --> 00:54:15.760
But they’re getting married in a few days, Dad.

00:54:20.960 --> 00:54:22.260
Let me take care of that.

00:54:24.900 --> 00:54:26.600
I’ll go talk to Din tomorrow.

00:54:33.300 --> 00:54:38.860
[Saen Rak farm]

00:54:40.300 --> 00:54:43.460
I’m thinking, maybe I should have my workers grow more flowers here.

00:54:43.660 --> 00:54:45.530
So that you’d feel more like home.

00:54:45.700 --> 00:54:46.800
What do you think?

00:54:47.560 --> 00:54:48.360
Thank you.

00:54:49.130 --> 00:54:51.400
Then, do you think we should…

00:54:51.400 --> 00:54:52.420
Din!

00:54:53.260 --> 00:54:54.780
Din!

00:54:55.500 --> 00:54:57.140
Din!

